Let $x = \arctan \left( \frac{a}{b + c} \right)$ and $y = \arctan \left( \frac{b}{a + c} \right).$  Then
\[\tan x = \frac{a}{b + c} \quad \text{and} \quad \tan y = \frac{b}{a + c}.\]From $\tan (x + y) = \frac{\tan x + \tan y}{1 - \tan x \tan y},$
\[\tan (x + y) = \frac{a}{b + c} + \frac{b}{a + c} - \frac{ab}{(b + c)(a + c)}.\]By the Pythagorean theorem,
\[a^2 + b^2 = c^2.\]Then $a^2 = c^2 - b^2,$ so
\[\frac{a}{b + c} = \frac{\sqrt{c^2 - b^2}}{b + c}.\]Similarly,
\[\frac{b}{a + c} = \frac{\sqrt{c^2 - a^2}}{a + c}.\]Hence,
\begin{align*}
\tan (x + y) &= \frac{\sqrt{c^2 - b^2}}{b + c} + \frac{\sqrt{c^2 - a^2}}{a + c} - \frac{ab}{(b + c)(a + c)} \\
&= \frac{(a + b)(a + c)(b + c) - abc - (b + c) \sqrt{c^2 - b^2} (a + c) - (a + b) \sqrt{c^2 - a^2} (b + c)}{(b + c)(a + c)(a + b)} \\
&= \frac{a^2 b + ab^2 + 2abc - abc - b \sqrt{c^2 - b^2} (a + c) - a \sqrt{c^2 - a^2} (b + c)}{(b + c)(a + c)(a + b)} \\
&= \frac{ab (a + b - \sqrt{c^2 - a^2} - \sqrt{c^2 - b^2})}{(b + c)(a + c)(a + b)}.
\end{align*}Finally, $x + y = \arctan \left( \frac{ab (a + b - \sqrt{c^2 - a^2} - \sqrt{c^2 - b^2})}{(b + c)(a + c)(a + b)} \right).$

